  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Preschool teacher",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<p>· Plan, supervise and implement the programme for the class in accordance with centre’s policies and framework.</p>\n<p>· Complete progress reports on children for each semester and prepares a developmental portfolio for each child.</p>\n<p>· Set up and create a stimulating and engaging pleasant learning environment that promotes self-directed learning.</p>\n<p>· Responsible for all aspects of classroom management and carry out routine care duties to ensure the safety and hygiene of the children.</p>\n<p>· Work closely with the other teaching staff in the class in carrying out the duties.</p>\n<p>· Build and maintain a close partnership with parents.</p>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<p>· Minimum Diploma in Early Childhood Care and Education</p>\n<p>· Certified by ECDA at L2 category</p>\n<p>· Excellent communication and interpersonal skills</p>\n<p>· Preferably have at least 1 year of relevant working experience in a preschool environment</p>\n<p>· A high tolerance level towards children is an advantage</p>\n<p>· Able to work well independently as well as within a team</p>",
